<section id="section-6">
<title> Summary </title>
<para id="element-98m"><term>1: </term> Angular quantities are general quantities, which can be defined and interpreted for any motion types – pure/impure translation or rotation.
</para>
<para id="element-98a"><term>2: </term>Angular velocity is defined as the time rate of change of angular displacement with respect to a point :
</para>
<para id="element-98as">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> ω </m:mi>
