</m:mrow>
<m:mrow>
<m:mo> d </m:mo> 
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> t </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
</m:mfrac>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math> </para>
<para id="element-98b"><term>3: </term>If the point, about which angular velocity is determined, is the origin of the reference system, then the position of the particle is represented by position vector.
 </para>
<para id="element-98c"><term>4: </term>The measurement and physical interpretation of angular velocity are different than that in the case of circular (rotational) motion about an axis.
 </para>

<para id="element-98e"><term>5: </term>The relation between linear and angular velocity has the following form,
 </para>
<para id="element-98f">
