" denotes tangential component of the velocity vector, which is perpendicular to the position vector. </para>
<para id="element-98l"><term>7:</term> Direction of angular velocity is perpendicular to the plane of motion. The plane of motion, however, may not be fixed like in the case of rotation. We define plane of motion, which contains origin (or point) and tangential component of velocity.</para>
